<L>__{exterior desert later}
<D>__{amelia carries debbie in her arms under the burning sun, following a cattle trail. mike walk behind, pale, sweaty. amelia looks to the horizon: there is no sign of the trucks.}
<L>__{exterior desert day}
<D>__{they are still walking. amelia can barely go on. she stops to rest. she is sweating copiously. mike also looks weak.}
<L>__{exterior desert later}
<D>__{the heat is strong and amelia is beaten. she looks for the shade of a cluster of mesquites and lays debbie down. then she turns to mike.}
<C>__{amelia}
<D>__{sweetie, i'm going to go look for help. stay here and don't move.}
<C>__{mike}
<D>__{i'm not staying here alone.}
<C>__{amelia}
<D>__{honey, you have to take care of debbie.}
<C>__{mike}
<D>__{i'm going with you. mike looks at her with imploring eyes. amelia caresses him.}
<C>__{amelia}
<D>__{i won't be long. i promise.}
